service.tut.pori.twitterjazz.reference

Class BackendService

  • java.lang.Object
    • service.tut.pori.twitterjazz.reference.BackendService

  • @HTTPService(name="tjrb")
public class BackendService
extends java.lang.Object
    Reference implementation for Back-end APIs. This class defines the APIs implemented by analysis back-end services. As a general note, the back-end should ignore any unknown elements it cannot process.

      • addTask

        @HTTPServiceMethod(name="addTask",
                   acceptedMethods="POST")
public void addTask(@HTTPMethodParameter(name="body",bodyParameter=true)
                                                                                                    InputStreamParameter xml)
        The request is to be sent in the body of POST method. The Content-Type header MUST be set to "text/xml". The character set MUST be UTF-8. For example, "Content-Type: text/xml; charset=UTF-8".

        POST /rest/tjrb/addTask
        Content-Type: text/xml; charset=UTF-8
